Question4: How to solve the problem of filament is not

adhered to the printing bed?

1) First check whether the hot bed has been properly leveled, if the

nozzle is too high from the hot bed, please re-level the hot bed;

2) Then make sure that the hot bed is properly heated to the right

temperature to ensure a sufficient adhesion between the filament

and the hot bed, such as 80℃ for PLA;

3) In addition, in order to ensure good adhesion between the

model and the platform, a raft can be added to the 3d model when

sliced in the Cura which can increase adhesion between the model

and the platform.
